More and more forces mobilized for giant strike
The League of Trade Unions and the Hungarian Federation of Trade Unions are forming their coordination committee on Friday for the indefinite duration of the strike starting on Monday.
On Saturday, a large protest assembly is held, on Monday - on the day of the referendum on the Health Insurance Act - the work stop begins.
Strike-related, significant traffic obstructions are expected, as rail transport is almost completely stopped, and the Budapest public transport companies (BKV) are also on strike until 1 p.m.
Details of the strike on Monday will be announced on Friday afternoon by the League of Trade Unions and the Federation of Trade Unions.
