Holiday days are not everywhere holidays
In Hungary, public holidays are strictly regulated by law, so that the practice of redistributing the working days around the holidays has now become established, but the coming year will give us less such days.
In the EU and in America, too, something else is understood as "celebratory holiday".
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between state holidays and work-free days.
Labour-free days are mostly church holidays, or are related to significant historical events.
For example, we are also celebrating New Year: both the last day of the old year and the first day of the new year are days without work - the latter alone so that the New Year celebrations can rest.
Throughout the year we have a total of fourteen holidays.
The state holidays are the 15th of March, which commemorates the revolution of 1848, and the 23rd of October, the memorial day of the revolution of 1956.
On 20 August the foundation of the state, on 1 May the work is celebrated, on 1 and 2 November we commemorate our dead.
In addition, there are two holidays each at Easter, Pentecost, and Christmas.
Since our state, national or religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, the practice of "working day postponement" has proven itself in cases where we would only work one day before or after the holiday.
The price of the extended weekends, however, is that we have to work very well on the Saturdays before, or go to school.
When this day, which falls before or after the holiday, is to be completed in the end, is fixed for long years by the Minister of Labour in a separate regulation.
The legislation applies equally to all employers and employees, public employees and civil servants.
Only companies and institutions in which the operation is continued without interruption, i.e. also on public holidays, are excluded.
This year, the working order is only somewhat confused by the holidays at the end of the year: from 24 December, life in this country will formally stand still, since most take time compensation for the days between Christmas and New Year's Eve, or the specially cancelled holiday.
Next year, more holidays fall into the middle of the week, or the end of the week, so that there will be less redispancies on the working days than this year.
The calendar is first "turned upside down" around the day of work, so that people can stay at home for four days at a time.
Saturday, April 26th will be a working day, so Friday, May 2nd can be a day of rest.
The second re-disposal is related to the holiday on October 23rd: On Saturday, October 18th, you will have to work Friday, October 24th in advance.
The end of the year, however, will be completely marked by the holidays, after everything will be settled and stopped from 24 December, even if New Year's Eve falls on a Wednesday.
Six deterrent little things to annoy colleagues
E-mails that we forget to send, voice messages that we never receive - harmless lies that we don't notice anymore: they bring "color" into everyday life at work.
The question is simply whether you get used to these minor inconveniences, or if you better face the challenge and try to avoid them deliberately, for other annoying situations.
Tips.
"Sorry, I forgot to tell you that someone from the marketing department called" - says a colleague.
That it missed a meeting?
At best, you regret it and try to make up for it by perhaps calling the marketing department and remorsefully confessing that you would have forgotten to align the message (this is the less common method).
Most of the time, it's done with an apology.
Before you get involved in embarrassing excuses, you should consider how you can really prepare unpleasant moments for your colleagues and try to avoid these situations consciously.
To borrow something that doesn't belong to you?
There's hardly anything more annoying than reaching for a document, office supplies, or the phone, but it's not there.
Yesterday the notebook was still on the desk - this morning it is gone?
Or is the lost ballpoint pen discovered on a colleague's desk?
Without asking, you should not borrow anything from your colleagues, because they are right to be upset when they find that something has gone away.
So, don't put any envelopes or post-it from the office in your pocket, because it could hit you yourself: no more there, if you really need it.
Talking about colleagues' private lives?
There is no effective means of stopping a gossip that has already been put into the world.
Who did what to who?
Where and why?
One should not tie the information (or conjecture) about the private life of the colleagues to everyone's nose if possible!
And if someone opens up and tells us his innermost secret, we should not abuse that trust!
It is best to keep silent like a grave, instead of directing those who are not present, even if others know about the problems of their colleague.
Reported sick for no reason?
If you call in the office to report yourself ill with painful headaches, because you are feeling uncomfortable or just want to rest, you should be aware of one thing: your own work, irreplaceable executions, projects with fixed appointments must now be done by your colleagues instead of yourself.
So don't mess with colleagues!
If you already know the day before that you won't make it to the office the next day, or that something could come in between, which is why you have to stay at home, you should report it in time so that neither the colleagues nor the boss are unexpectedly confronted with the absence.
Summing up, giggles, phone calls
We are in the middle of our work, but are we suddenly disturbed by the loud giggling of our colleagues?
Inadvertently listening to a phone call you shouldn't have heard?
One should not bother the colleagues with buzzing, singing, loud conversations (which one leads over their heads), trampling, constant scolding or nagging.
All of this can be very disturbing, even if they are not exactly deepened in a task (writing, planning, organizing).
Is it always the others' fault?
If a project is not completed on time, you have forgotten to send an important letter or important messages, you should not look for the guilt of your own forgetfulness with others!
If possible, do not talk about the chaos in the office or the noisy colleagues!
The best way to admit your mistakes is to apologize if others were affected!
The question of how to make up for the mistake or make up for the missing is all too appropriate!
In the office - a feeling like at home?
Training Pants and Slaps: Comfortable for home, but has nothing to lose in the office!
Not even then should you dress so casually, if the workplace would actually allow it!
Just don't get too sloppy - you should respect both your colleagues and yourself to the extent that you dress in the office - if desired, also pretty and elegant!
To make it right for everyone - or how to become uninteresting for others
Stop and go traffic, the car in the middle of every morning traffic jam.
From the radio sounds a strange melody: the sound of a violin, paired with electronic effects.
I'm turning the volume up.
The tempo changes, to the previous sounds comes the bass, and as a real sound jewel a female choir.
It is the song "Wings of Love" by Zagar, which sounds on mr2.
The local music scene hasn't spoiled us with high-quality electropop for a long time.
But now you even see the traffic jam differently when you hear the new album from Zagar.
The appearance of Yonderboi, so many new and exciting productions from the domestic digital underground scene are slowly contributing to a change in the overall picture, and even if the garage rock with its guitar squeak is "in" again, the domestic electropop proves: There are new things under the sun.
Balázs Zságer started in Pécs, playing in the band Yonderboi himself, before he started to walk his own way - perhaps because a tavern can't handle two pipers.
The breakthrough with his project (Zagar) and his music, which merges elements from jazz, electronic, and pop, was only achieved when one approached him with the request to compose the soundtrack for a film (e.g.
"Szezon" by Ferenc Török).
The formation, which had initially appeared in smaller clubs, only became known to the wider audience when the magazine "wan2" ranked their first album from 2002 among the top 50 domestic albums and Zagar, together with Yonderboi, became almost the only trendsetter, also marketable in the West.
No doubt Zagar and his band were "trendy", but no one was interested in whether they would like to wear this brand.
The band reacted as it should: With a new, even better album.
The new album with the title "Cannot Walk Fly Instead" could open up new paths for them, but the title already expresses the desire for continuity with the Pécs years.
The expression comes from the time when Balázs Zságer was still on the road with another band.
The airy, flying allusion would also be fine, but in addition to the ethereal character of the music, the louder guitar, the influences of rock'n'roll - corresponding to the zeitgeist and the trends - stand out.
With these songs, singer György Ligeti, who lives in England and works with the band "The Puzzle", introduced himself at the premiere at Millenáris.
A song from the album even made it to the radio hit - the mr2 Petőfi, which has been broadcasting pop music from early to late, has gradually set the listener with the number "Wings of Love", which was recorded with the participation of six local singers ("Underground Divas").
So everything's fine (?).
The hvg.hu asked Balázs Zságer.
hvg.hu: This new hit raises the question: To what extent is your music reserved for a certain layer?
Balázs Zságer: The term "shift music" doesn't mean much to me.
In my opinion, there are two boxes in pop music, not mainstream and underground, or alternative and pop, but commercial and honest.
Even the so-called alternative or underground music can be shallow and meaningless, but they can also only be produced for sale, which makes them commercial music.
Also a good pop number can arise from an honest motive.
The listener's willingness to accept also works according to this principle, independent of languages and national borders.
hvg.hu: Do you see a difference in the openness of the Hungarian and foreign audiences to your music?
B. Zs.: In foreign countries, especially west of us, pop music has a greater tradition.
Not only teenagers or Twens go to concerts, but also the older audience.
They follow the trends in pop music that are happening around them much more attentively, because they also consider them to be part of contemporary culture.
hvg.hu: What role does the audience play in your work?
Is it important who, where, how many listen to your music?
B. Zs.: Of course it is a good feeling to see more and more coming to our concerts.
But we never composed for the market.
With us, music does not arise to serve a purpose, but for a specific reason.
The role of the audience is usually felt at the concerts, where there is already a mutual interaction, but that is only in the incomprehensible changes of the moment.
Nevertheless, I have noticed that if you want to make it right for everyone, you are no longer interesting.
hvg.hu: How far do you want to follow the example of Yonderboi?
He is on the road as a soloist and has built his career more in the West.
B. Zs.: We don't really go his way, not to mention trying to interpret this into our music over and over again.
We see ourselves as more of a team player who trusts in the musical presence of the other and lets them unfold.
At the beginning, of course, comparisons of our work with Yonderboi's were inevitable, as several of us came out of his band and took another path.
hvg.hu: In the charts of mr2 Petőfi "Wings of Love" comes first.
Many have only heard the name Zagar in connection with this number.
Was the opening deliberately staged with a somewhat more popular style towards a wider audience?
B. Zs.: We had no plans to write a hit, which is supposed to be a draw horse for the album.
This song is about more.
It was meant as the finale of the album, with which we wanted to dissolve the sound orgy and the somewhat more difficult topics.
hvg.hu: How did you choose the six singers?
Why them, what was the guiding principle?
B. Zs.: The basic idea was to make a gospel-like choir.
Then came the idea to assemble the choir from talented soloists of the domestic music scene.
This is how the six-member choir was formed - namely Sena, Edina Kutzora, Judie Jay, Bori Péterfy, Enikő Hodosi [Neo], Juci Németh - which we then baptized apately "Underground Divas".
hvg.hu: Did you want the song to be the same, or did the girls help shape it?
B. Zs.: The number has been in the instrumental version for a long time, but when the material for the album was finished, we thought that this number still "needs something".
The chord sequence has formally demanded a vocal voice.
I sang the melody the same night, later they learned the girls.
It all came practically straight away and frighteningly spontaneous.
I remember I was pretty electrified back then, but it was already the "Divas" needed.
With my voice alone, the song would never have become so strong.
hvg.hu: On the record as well as at the concert one had the impression, however, that the girls were in the background.
There is no solo part (apart from Judy Jay's short solo), they have no role of their own, sing together completely and are not louder than the music, so their singing is not only accompanied by the music.
They also stood on the stage in the back.
Is it intentional?
B.Zs.: That they stood in the back was because of purely technical problems.
However, we deliberately did not want to give them solo roles.
The number is also about forgetting a little about your ego, forgetting who came from and where to go, let's just let these particular wings, the wings of love lift us up.
I would like others to also feel this euphoric state that we felt when the song came into being.
hvg.hu: What was the most elaborate song?
B. Zs.: In musical creative work actually none at all, there were rather more difficult tasks when mixing.
For example in "Dorian Gray's Dilemma", where I play on a concert piano, or in "Rock'n'Roll Goes To The Girls", where the groove did not want to work for a longer time, but gradually everything joined together, like in a puzzle.
hvg.hu: What is your favorite number from the new album?
B. Zs.: This changes with the concerts constantly and also now, where I "let go" the album.
At present it is "Prophet Is A Fool", "Escape From The Earth" and the number "Never The Same".
