The Congress agrees with the MIFID directive, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel with the parliamentary drafting, which ended its session today with the Congress resolution in the Senate on the amendments to the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law with the intention of allowing the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the congressmen and senate members, who in their negotiations and votes had the aim of establishing the best possible regulation, which guarantees the security of investors and regulates the individual entrepreneurial activities, in order to guarantee a generally efficient market situation.
In addition to the modernisation of financial markets, the MIFID, which is redefining the Investment Services Regulation, is pursuing an improvement in investor protection, an increase in the right of control of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and the promotion of cooperation between the various control authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive allows financial advisory services to be offered to both specialised firms and natural or legal persons, and also contributes to the establishment of new financial services companies (ESIS), the consulting companies which are affiliated with investment and brokerage companies in securities.
It also increases the number of systems for the execution of financial transactions, adding to the regulated circulation markets the multilateral systems of the securities business and the systems for the internationalisation of trading orders, which would eventually compete with the current economic operators.
