Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible case of damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which again depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of drawing up the driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you have to be clear about what we're dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which shall stipulate that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to submit the corresponding severance payment in the event of a claim.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance, which consists of several factors, including age, gender, time of drawing up the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that if there is a higher risk of accidents, higher contributions will also be payable.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women have to pay less contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the firm's conviction, they tend to have fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefits attributed to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In drawing up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that suits his personal needs most.
We now list at this point the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance policy in order to be able to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
Under 25-year-olds face numerous obstacles to the choice of low-cost insurance, such as low driving practice and a young driver's license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out comprehensive insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a comprehensive with excess, so that the services of a comprehensive insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer has to pay part of the amount incurred by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, main representative of Spain at First Europa, a brokerage company for online insurance.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused to his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is up to you to lower the insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate with the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the above rates.
The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its revenues.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can allow itself to increase the bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it is most appropriate to opt for a comprehensive insurance with a deductible.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, either in the event of an accident or at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been dropped.
Nevertheless, for a married customer who has no children, it is advisable to take out comprehensive insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the corresponding person permits it.
On the part of the insurers, married couples with children are considered to have the lowest accident rate, and accordingly their contributions are also low.
In this case, a comprehensive insurance with a deductible (with an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the case that one has received a high credit, an extended insurance, which starts only for the third year of the vehicle, is recommended.
They are more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power which allows them to pay a higher contribution, notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners it is advisable to take out a comprehensive insurance with a deductible (with an amount of 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only uses with a sufficiently high credit.
In the end, it is important to note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accident damage, but also because it has high costs, which require a thorough selection, which corresponds to our personal situation.
