Two months ago, when the Prime Minister withdrew from the demand for an election, in a stupid way insulting the intelligence of the British, claiming that opinion polls did not influence this decision, there was hope that he would offer a robust, efficient government.
Instead, as Vince Cable, the increasingly perceptive chairman of the Liberal Democrats, put it, the once feared Brown of Stalin has evolved into Mr. Bean.
